uld require POST + CSRF token or explicit user confirmation.\n- **Second priority**: localStorage is used for both non-sensitive (session timing) and sensitive data (encryption salt). XSS anywhere on the origin can read/modify both.\n- **Architectural note**: The app's local-first design is sound, but the reliance on localStorage for secrets is inherently weak. The PBKDF2 + AES-GCM implementation is solid; the salt storage is the weak link.\n- **No hardcoded credentials** found; the mocked LMS data is safe. The build scripts are low risk (no user input).\n",
